<li>175 , No. 3 , November 6 , 2006 453 -- 463 http://www.jcb.org/cgi/doi/10.1083/jcb.200605144 JCB 453 Results Differential activation of Cdc42 and Rac1 by Salmonella effector-proteins in vivo Previous studies have established that the cytoskeletal remodeling driving Salmonella entry into nonphagocytic cells is triggered by three bacterial effector-proteins ( SopE , SopE2 , and SopB ) that , upon delivery into host cells , target the Rho family GTPases Cdc42 and Rac1 ( Hardt et al. , 1998 ; Bakshi et al. , 2000 ; Stender et al. , 2000 ; Zhou et al. , 2001 ) .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=17074883" target="_blank">17074883</a>]<br></li>
