<li>Jank , T. , Bogdanović , X. , Wirth , C. , Haaf , E. , Spoerner , M. , Böhmer , K. E. , Steinemann , M. , Orth , J. H. , Kalbitzer , H. R. , Warscheid , B. , Hunte , C. , and Aktories , K. ( 2013 ) A bacterial toxin catalyzing tyrosine glycosylation of Rho and deamidation of G and G proteins .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=29449376" target="_blank">29449376</a>]<br></li>
<li>Cdc42 and Rac1 , but not tyrosine kinases or PI-3K , are required for Salmonella-induced apoptosis in U937 cells Salmonella infections are known to activate a variety of host cell signaling pathways , including Rho -- GTPases , tyrosine kinase , PI-3K , and Akt [ 22 -- 25 , 41 , 42 ] , which are well-estab-lished regulators of apoptosis [ 21 , 43 -- 45 ] .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12960245" target="_blank">12960245</a>]<br></li>
<li>In contrast , phagocytosis of opsonized Salmonella by U937 cells did not induce apoptosis , but it did activate the mentioned Rho -- GTPases in a tyrosine kinase - and PI-3K-dependent manner .	[<a href="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/?term=12960245" target="_blank">12960245</a>]<br></li>
